+{"id":"frankentorch-kae4","title":"Padding modules sever autograd via tensor_values + non-grad rebuild","description":"ReflectionPad1d, ReflectionPad2d, ReplicationPad1d, ReplicationPad2d, ReplicationPad3d, CircularPad1d, CircularPad2d in ft-nn all extract tensor_values from input, manually permute/copy to a new layout, then rebuild via session.tensor_variable(values, shape, false). This silently severs autograd through every padding module — gradients can't flow back to the input. Breaks training for any model using reflection/replication/circular padding (CNNs, U-Nets, GANs, audio models).

Fix: replace each implementation with a tensor_index_select-based composition that is autograd-aware. The padding operation is mathematically just a structured gather along the spatial dimension(s); index_select handles the gather-then-scatter backward correctly. For multi-dimensional pads (2D/3D), apply index_select sequentially along each axis.

